		</li>
		</ul>
</div>
<div class="box left">
<h3>My process</h3>
</div>
<div class="box right">
<p>I strongly believe we can&#8217;t look to the future without understanding our present. Context, in all it forms, shapes our ability to foresee what&#8217;s next. Design should embrace science and art, stand on the shoulders of technology and look deeply into our history to create a story we can all relate to, creating new knowledge from experience.</p>
<blockquote><p>“Design is not added value; design is value” — Gui Bonsiepe</p></blockquote>
<p>My background begins with the Ulm Model and grows every day through visionaries such as Bruno Latour, Tomás Maldonado or Gui Bonsiepe.</p>
<p>My work philosophy starts with simple steps that transform every project into a learning experience, both for me and my clients or colleagues.</p>
<ol>
<li>Understand</li>
<li>Plan</li>
<li>Involve</li>
<li>Research</li>
<li>Instrumentalize</li>
<li>Prototype</li>
<li>Test</li>
<li>Develop</li>
<li>Deliver</li>
<li>Refine</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="box left">
<h3>Contact me</h3>
</div>
<div class="box right">
<p>Right now, I&#8217;m looking to work with amazing people and in meaningful projects, if you think someone like me would be a good fit, let me know!.</p>
<p><em>—<br />
</em>+56 9 4946 0085<br />
<a href="mailto:hello@pablonoel.com"> hello@pablonoel.com<br />
</a>Santiago, Chile</p>
</div>
<div class="box center">
<p>All photos featured in this website are mine, except where noted.<br />
Profile photos by <a href="http://fernandarequena.com">Fernanda Requena</a></p>
